  "text": "The grid [CITATION_1] n contains large \"cliques\": sets of points in which any two are collinear. In such a clique, the number of monochromatic pairs is least when the colors are balanced, and even then is close to 1 2 . Thus, we expect that for at least some lengths k, q(k) > 1 2 − ǫ for some ǫ that goes to 0 with n. This intuition is correct in a way that we will make more precise.",
